Important



If you are eligible for Affiliate status, your supervisor or research sponsor must register as an Authorized Investigator BEFORE you may request affiliate access from them. Communicate with your sponsor about your request.

Databrary is designed by and for researchers. This section aims to provide researchers guidance about how to use Databrary.
A common first step is to determine your status as a researcher. See the About Databrary section for details Then, you can request authorization as described in the next chapter.
I am eligible to become an Authorized Investigator if:

I can conduct independent research;

I can submit funding proposals as the lead investigator;

I have Principal Investigator (PI) status or a tenure-track faculty position at my Institution; –&gt;
My Institution maintains or uses an ethics board to review and approve research involving human subjects (or animals where relevant); AND –&gt;
I have current training that addresses research ethics with human subject (or animals where relevant)

I conduct research under the supervision of an Authorized Investigator’s sponsorship or someone who is eligible to become an Authorized Investigator;
I am a student, research staff, or post-doctoral researcher.
I have current training that addresses research ethics with human subjects (e.g.CITI training.

I conduct independent, unsupervised, research at my institution;
I submit funding proposals as lead investigator;
I have Principal Investigator (PI) status or hold a tenure-track faculty position at my institution;
My institution maintains or uses an ethics board to review and approve research involving human subjects (or non-human animals where relevant);
I have current training that addresses research ethics with human subject (e.g. CITI training);
I would like to reuse or upload data to Databrary.
I sponsor and supervise lab staff and students who work on my projects or on collaborative projects, and I have authority to supervise their access to data that I share or or others have shared on Databrary.

Researchers conduct independent, unsupervised, research at the institution;
Researchers submit funding proposals as lead investigator;
Researchers have Principal Investigator (PI) status or hold a tenure-track faculty position at the institution;
Researchers have current training that addresses research ethics with human subject (e.g. CITI training);
Researchers wish to download and reuse or upload data to Databrary.
